HEADWORD: Midas
<hw>Mi"das</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from L.
<ets>Midas</ets>, a man fabled to have had ass's ears.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of longeared South American monkeys,
including numerous species of marmosets. See
<er>Marmoset</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midas's ear</ent>⟦br⟧
